title: Alvito
subtitle: Town in Portugal
text: Alvito is a town and a municipality in Beja District in Portugal. The population in 2011 was 2,504, in an area of 264.85 km². The current mayor is António João Feio Valério.

title: Amherst
subtitle: Town in Massachusetts
text: Amherst is a town in Hampshire County, Massachusetts, United States, in the Connecticut River valley. As of the 2010 census, the population was 37,819, making it the highest populated municipality in Hampshire County.

title: Araçatuba
subtitle: City in Brazil
text: Araçatuba is a city located in the northwest of São Paulo state, Brazil. The city has 190,536 inhabitants and 1,167.4 km² of area. The city name comes from the Tupi language and means "abundance of araçá". Araçatuba is located 532 km from the city of São Paulo and 11 km from Birigui.

title: Autrans
subtitle: Commune in France
text: Autrans is a former commune in the Isère department in the Rhône-Alpes region of south-eastern France. On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune of Autrans-Méaudre-en-Vercors.

title: Blainville-sur-Mer
subtitle: Commune in France
text: Blainville-sur-Mer is a commune in the Manche department in the Normandy region in northwestern France.

title: Bruck an der Mur
subtitle: City in Austria
text: Bruck an der Mur is a city of some 13,500 people located in the district Bruck-Mürzzuschlag, in the Austrian state of Styria. It is located at the confluence of the Mur and Mürz Rivers. Its manufacturing includes metal products and paper.

title: Cabanatuan
subtitle: City in the Philippines
text: Cabanatuan, officially the City of Cabanatuan, or simply Cabanatuan City is a 1st class city in the province of Nueva Ecija, Philippines. According to the 2015 census, it has a population of 302,231 people, making it the most populous city in Nueva Ecija and the fifth-most populous in Central Luzon.

title: Cambará do Sul
subtitle: Municipality in Brazil
text: Cambará do Sul is a municipality in the state of Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil. Its population was approximately 6,600 in 2010. It has an area of approximately 1212 km². The city is one of the coldest in Brazil and sometimes there is chance of snow.

title: Castellare-di-Casinca
subtitle: Commune in France
text: Castellare-di-Casinca is a commune in the Haute-Corse department of France on the island of Corsica.

title: Cochrane
subtitle: Town in Canada
text: Cochrane is a town in the Canadian province of Alberta. The town is located 18 km west of the Calgary city limits along Highway 1A. Cochrane is one of the fastest growing communities in Canada, and with a population of 29,277 in 2019, it is one of the largest towns in Alberta.

title: Creuzburg
subtitle: Town in Germany
text: Creuzburg is a town on the Werra river in the Wartburgkreis in Thuringia, Germany.

title: Dramalj
subtitle: Village in Croatia
text: Dramalj is a village in Croatia. It is part of the town of Crikvenica, extending from the neighborhood Crni mol to the tourist complex Kačjak. Dramalj has 1,485 inhabitants, most of whom are engaged in tourism and catering industry.

title: Drumheller
subtitle: Town in Canada
text: Drumheller is a town northeast of Calgary, in Alberta, Canada. On the edge of town, in Midland Provincial Park, the Royal Tyrrell Museum contains a large collection of dinosaur fossils. Downtown, stairs wind inside the “World’s Largest Dinosaur,” a giant model T-Rex with views from its jaw. To the southeast, the Atlas Coal Mine National Historic Site explores the Drumheller Valley’s coal-mining heritage.

title: Erdek
subtitle: Town in Turkey
text: Erdek is a town and district of Balıkesir Province in the Marmara region of Turkey. The population was 34000 in 2010. Located on the north coast of Gulf of Erdek at the south of the Sea of Marmara, Erdek is known as a holiday destination that is popular among domestic tourists.

title: Ermenonville
subtitle: Commune in France
text: Ermenonville is a commune in Oise, France. Ermenonville is notable for its park named for Jean-Jacques Rousseau by René Louis de Girardin. Rousseau's tomb was designed by the painter Hubert Robert, and sits on the Isle of Poplars in its lake.

title: Fabriano
subtitle: Town in Italy
text: Fabriano is a town and comune of Ancona province in the Italian region of the Marche, at 325 metres above sea level. It lies in the Esino valley 44 kilometres upstream and southwest of Jesi; and 15 kilometres east-northeast of Fossato di Vico and 36 kilometres east of Gubbio. Its location on the main highway and rail line from Umbria to the Adriatic make it a mid-sized regional center in the Apennines. Fabriano is the headquarters of the giant appliance maker Indesit. Fabriano, with Bologna, is the only Italian creative city. The town is in the category Folk Arts.

title: Futaleufú
subtitle: Town in Chile
text: Futaleufú is a Chilean town and commune located in Northern Patagonia, specifically in Palena Province, Los Lagos Region. Futaleufu is a frontier town with a small but growing tourism industry based on adventure tourism—most specifically whitewater rafting—but also fishing, mountain biking, trekking, and canyoning.

title: Haynsburg
subtitle: Village in Germany
text: Haynsburg is a village and a former municipality in the Burgenlandkreis district, in Saxony-Anhalt, Germany. Since 1 January 2010, it is part of the municipality Wetterzeube.

title: Horb am Neckar
subtitle: Town in Germany
text: Horb am Neckar is a town in the southwest of the German state of Baden-Württemberg. It is located on the Neckar river, between Offenburg to the west and Tübingen to the east.

title: Knaresborough
subtitle: Town in England
text: Knaresborough is a market and spa town and civil parish in the Borough of Harrogate, North Yorkshire, England, on the River Nidd 4 miles east of Harrogate.

title: La Savina
subtitle: Village in Formentera, Spain
text: La Savina or La Sabina is a port village in Formentera, on the Balearic Islands, off eastern Spain. The Far de la Savina lighthouse is located nearby.

title: La Tzoumaz
subtitle: Ski resort in the Swiss Alps
text: La Tzoumaz is a ski resort in the Swiss Alps, in the canton of Valais. It is part of the "Four Valleys" ski area, which consists of various ski resorts, including Verbier, Nendaz, Veysonnaz, La Tzoumaz, and Thyon. As such it has direct access to over 400 km of runs.

title: Merkem
subtitle: Town in Belgium
text: Merkem is a town in the Belgian province West-Flanders. It is a part of the municipality of Houthulst.

title: New Lisbon
subtitle: City in Wisconsin
text: New Lisbon is a city in Juneau County, Wisconsin, United States. The population was 2,554 at the 2010 census.

title: Nogueira de Ramuín
subtitle: Municipality in Spain
text: Nogueira de Ramuín is a municipality in the province of Ourense in the Galicia region of north-west Spain. The municipality consists of 13 parroquias, the capital being Luintra.

title: Nordhastedt
subtitle: Municipality in Germany
text: Nordhastedt is a municipality in the district of Dithmarschen, in Schleswig-Holstein, Germany.

title: Piaseczno
subtitle: Town in Poland
text: Piaseczno is a town in central Poland with 47,660 inhabitants. It is situated in the Masovian Voivodeship, approximately 16 kilometres south of Warsaw. It is a popular residential area and a suburb of Warsaw and is strongly linked to the capital, both economically and culturally. It is the capital of Piaseczno County.

title: Posada de Valdeón
subtitle: Municipality in Spain
text: Posada de Valdeón is a municipality located in the province of León, Castile and León, Spain.

title: Pulau Sibu
subtitle: Island in Mersing, Malaysia
text: Sibu Island is an island group in Mersing District, Johor, Malaysia.

title: Raunheim
subtitle: Town in Germany
text: Raunheim is a town in Groß-Gerau district in Hesse, Germany and a part of the Frankfurt Urban Region as well as the Frankfurt Rhein-Main Region.

title: Reynosa
subtitle: City in Mexico
text: Reynosa is a border city in the northern part of the state of Tamaulipas, in Mexico. It is also the municipal seat of Reynosa Municipality. The city is located on the southern bank of the Rio Grande in the international Reynosa–McAllen Metropolitan Area, directly across of the Mexico-U.S. border from Hidalgo, Texas.

title: Rohrdorf
subtitle: Municipality in Germany
text: Rohrdorf is a municipality in the district of Rosenheim in Upper Bavaria, Germany. It is located in the Inn valley.

title: Runnemede
subtitle: Township in New Jersey
text: Runnemede is a borough in Camden County, New Jersey, United States. As of the 2010 United States Census, the borough's population was 8,468, reflecting a decline of 65 from the 8,533 counted in the 2000 Census, which had in turn declined by 509 from the 9,042 counted in the 1990 Census.

title: Saint Francisville
subtitle: Town in Louisiana
text: St. Francisville is a town in, and the parish seat of, West Feliciana Parish, Louisiana, United States. The population was 1,712 at the 2000 census. It is part of the Baton Rouge Metropolitan Statistical Area.

title: San José de las Matas
subtitle: Municipality in the Dominican Republic
text: San José de las Matas, also known as Sajoma, is a municipality of the Santiago province in the Dominican Republic. Within the municipality there are three municipal districts: El Rubio, La Cuesta and Las Placetas.

title: Šonov
subtitle: Village in the Czech Republic
text: Šonov is a village and municipality in Náchod District in the Hradec Králové Region of the Czech Republic. It is located near the border with Poland.

title: Stavropol
subtitle: City in Russia
text: Stavropol is a city in southwestern Russia. The central Stavropol State Museum-Reserve includes exhibitions on archaeology, paleontology and Russian history. Works at the nearby Stavropol Regional Museum of Fine Arts include religious icons and sculpture. To the west, the Stavropol Botanical Garden has water lilies and tree-lined paths. Vast Pobedy Park, or Victory Park, features rides, plus old planes and tanks.

title: Swalmen
subtitle: Town in the Netherlands
text: Swalmen is a town in the south-eastern Netherlands. The town is situated between the German border and the Meuse river. Until 1 January 2007, Swalmen was a separate municipality, covering the villages Swalmen, Asselt and Boukoul. These are now part of the municipality of Roermond.

title: Viareggio
subtitle: City in Italy
text: Viareggio, a seaside city in Tuscany, Italy, is known for its Carnival. La Cittadella is a complex housing the Carnival Museum, with small reproductions of the city’s allegorical floats. The Villa Paolina Civic Museums include a museum of musical instruments and an archaeological museum. To the southeast, in the town of Torre del Lago, is Villa Puccini, a museum about the composer in his former lakeside residence.

title: Weehawken
subtitle: Township in New Jersey
text: Weehawken is a township in the northern part of Hudson County, New Jersey, United States. As of the 2010 United States Census, the township's population was 12,554, reflecting a decline of 947 from the 13,501 counted in the 2000 Census, which had in turn increased by 1,116 from the 12,385 counted in the 1990 Census.

title: White Haven
subtitle: Borough in Luzerne County, Pennsylvania
text: White Haven is a borough in Luzerne County, Pennsylvania. It is located along the Lehigh River. The population was 1,097 at the 2010 census.
